	<owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/biopharma/PSOAClassLevelMappingExample">
		<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">PSOA Class Level Mapping Example Ontology</rdfs:label>
		<dcterms:abstract>This example mapping file demonstrates an application-level implementation in which selected planned process classes are aligned to PSOA levels through class-level SubClassOf axioms using the relation prescribed by. The example reflects industry member knowledge and shows how classification with respect to the recipe process element structure can be achieved by asserting that a planned process class is prescribed by some recipe process element at a particular level. It thereby illustrates the use of the recipe process element occurrence-based utility classification classes from the Recipe Process Element Occurrence Utility Module, which support reasoning across the four PSOA levels: recipe process, recipe process stage, recipe process operation, and recipe process action. The applicable PSOA level is then visible in the inferred hierarchy through the corresponding PSOA occurrences. Although the mapping is informed from a general and site recipe perspective, no general or site recipe is implemented in this file. Rather, that perspective serves as background for the selected mappings shown here. This example focuses specifically on class-level typing as one possible approach to using the utility classification classes. It is not intended to prescribe class-level typing as the only or preferred pattern in all cases. Additional example files are planned to illustrate complementary approaches, including individual-level typing and recipe-based class extensions. Guidance on the use of recipe process element occurrence-based utility classes is also being prepared to support consistent application and interpretation of this pattern.</dcterms:abstract>
		<dcterms:contributor>Adlane Rebai, Millipore Sigma</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Ana Nikolov, OAGi</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Boonserm Kulvatunyou, NIST</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Cameron Gibbs, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Gabriela Henning, NIST</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Marie-Aude Coutouly, Millipore Sigma</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Melissa Weller, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Milos Drobnjakovic, OAGi</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Stephen J. Granite, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Stephen Kahmann, CrownPoint Technologies, LLC</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:license rdf:datatype="&xsd;anyURI">http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT</dcterms:license>
		<owl:imports rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/202601/biopharma/RecipeProcessOccurrenceClassificationUtility/"/>
		<owl:imports rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/biopharma/ManufacturingExecution/"/>
		<owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/202601/biopharma/PSOAClassLevelMappingExample"/>
		<iof-av:copyright>Copyright (c) 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025, 2026 Open Applications Group</iof-av:copyright>
		<iof-av:maturity rdf:resource="&iof-ind;Released"/>
	</owl:Ontology>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&iof-construct;CaptureStep">
